<TEXT>
rep barney frank is offering an apology to 
political supporters and assuring them that my judgment has 
improved since his involvement with a male prostitute 
i made some serious mistakes in judgment several years ago 
what i did was wrong the massachusetts democrat said in a letter 
mailed friday to homestate supporters and volunteers in his 
previous campaigns for congress 
it did not affect my public decisions or any public business 
frank wrote but i regret that some of my past personal actions 
are troubling to people who placed their confidence in me 
frank also drew some republican support friday for his decision 
not to resign while awaiting an inquiry by the house ethics 
committee into his 18month relationship with stephen l gobie 
he deserves a fair hearing said rep newt gingrich of 
georgia the house republican whip 
gingrich who is under investigation by the ethics committee over 
his personal finances in a book deal told reporters it was 
appropriate for frank to await the panels findings 
frank is a fiveterm congressman and outspoken liberal who was 
reelected overwhelmingly in 1988 after disclosing the year before 
that he is homosexual 
gobie has charged he operated a prostitution ring out of franks 
capitol hill apartment frank has acknowledged paying gobie for sex 
and then hiring him as a personal assistant and driver but says he 
threw gobie out when he learned of the prostitution operation that 
was shortly before frank publicly disclosed he is homosexual 
frank in his letter said the pressure of hiding his 
homosexuality while maintaining a political life led him to deal 
with the prostitute 
dealing with being gay while continuing to meet my public 
obligations created tremendous internal pressures frank wrote 
those pressures ended when i spoke publicly about my own personal 
identity not coincidentally my judgment has improved since then 
frank said that as a result of being in public life i cannot 
be surprised that my mistakes in personal judgment of several years 
ago have now become public knowledge but he said that some 
highly sensationalized stories about the matter have included 
substantial untruths 
it was to end any question about what is the truth that i asked 
the ethics committee of the united states congress to consider this 
entire matter he wrote i need hardly tell you that this 
committee will have my full cooperation meanwhile i hope you will 
accept my apology 
aides to frank said the letter was widely distributed to veteran 
supporters and was not mailed at government expense 
