finance officials of the worlds seven biggest 
economic powers met today amid renewed calls for the bush 
administration to curb the us budget deficit as its contribution 
toward stabilizing world currency markets 
treasury secretary nicholas f brady and federal reserve chairman 
alan greenspan hosted the private talks at the blair house across 
