seeking no further increase 
a strong dollar hurts us efforts to reduce its trade deficit 
because it raises the price of american exports overseas and makes 
foreign goods cheaper in the united states 
the dollars rise since the spring has come in the face of 
repeated and heavy selling by the g7 nations central banks in an 
effort to drive its value down 
