<TEXT>
a slight temblor jolted downtown los angeles 
on saturday about two hours after another minor quake shook an area 
east of the city but no injuries or damages were reported 
the ceiling shook a little bit and the desks shook a few 
seconds said los angeles county sheriffs spokesman deputy van 
mosely 
the afternoon earthquake measured 24 on the richter scale said 
hall daily of the california institute of technology in pasadena 
its epicenter was about three miles north of downtown and six miles 
southsouthwest of pasadena he said 
about two hours earlier a quake measuring 29 on the richer 
scale shook an area about 55 miles east of los angeles near rialto 
in san bernardino county daily said 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by ground motion recorded on a seismograph 
every increase of one number on the scale means that the ground 
motion is 10 times greater 
a quake of magnitude 2 is the smallest normally felt by humans 
a quake of magnitude 35 can cause slight damage in populated areas 
